    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1849-08-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1849-08-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="243" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Commandant <persName type="from">Newton</persName>, United States Navy, to Lieutenant-Commander
                                        <persName type="to">Totten</persName>, United States
                                    Navy.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Sealed orders.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1849-08-20">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">August</hi> 20, 1849</date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: You will proceed direct with the
                                United States steamer Water Witch, under your command, to Cat
                                Island, and there join the United States ship Albany, Commodore V.
                                M. Randolph, and assist him in carrying out the instructions of the
                                honorable Secretary of the Navy, a copy of which accompanies
                                this.</p>
                <p>Should you not fall in with the Albany at Cat Island, or its
                                vicinity, you will proceed to Balize, in further pursuance of the
                                orders.</p>
                <p>Wishing you a pleasant cruise, I am, very respectfully, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>JOHN THOMAS NEWTON,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Commandant.</hi>
                            </item>
                            <item>Lieutenant-Commander <hi rend="smallcaps">Geo. M.
                                                Totten</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">United States
                                                Steamer Water Witch.</hi>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
